id: pm-er4q
title: pm test --add causes immediate history drift via null timeout_seconds
description: "Reproduction: in a fresh tracker, `pm create` + `pm test <id> --add 'node scripts/run-tests.mjs test'` triggers history_drift_hash_mismatch immediately. Root cause: `sortTests` in src/core/item/item-format.ts:606 assigns `timeout_seconds: value.timeout_seconds` without coercing null to undefined. After TOON round-trip the field comes back as `null`, so canonicalDocument of the reloaded item produces `{command, scope, timeout_seconds: null}` whereas the patch chain records `{command, scope}` — break of replay parity. Verified by hand on Node 25.9.0 with pm 2026.5.14."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,bug,history,pm-cli,test-command
created_at: "2026-05-17T19:19:21.079Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T19:45:27.186Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: 1) Repro sequence (create + test --add) produces history_drift=ok 2) sortTests coerces null->undefined symmetric to file load 3) regression test added
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Fixed linked-test timeout_seconds normalization so absent timeouts do not persist as null and break history replay.
expected_result: Fresh create plus pm test --add without timeout_seconds verifies clean history and does not trigger history_drift_hash_mismatch.
actual_result: Regression and dogfood runs verified linked-test history replay remains clean; full release gate passed.
